HELLO!

Looking for 1-3 roommates
or a room to fill in Brooklyn/bushwick

Preferably queer people!!

Moving to NYC from Detroit in a few weeks and looking to be settled into a spot by March.

There are 2 units in my sisters 3 unit apartment building in bushwick that sound like a great deal to me.

1st floor: 4 bedrooms with built in lofted beds, 2 bathrooms(1 bathtub), backyard access, exposed brick.

2nd floor: 3 bedrooms, 1 bathroom, exposed brick.

Both around $2,700 total + utilities.

Also down to fill a room/look for different apartments with the right roommates.

Me: Queer artist who is into fashion, sewing, embroidery and other forms of visual art. CLEAN, 420 friendly, down to trade books and cook roommate dinners. My budget is $800 for a room.

Artists encouraged to inquire!

Can provide a video that my sister took of the first floor or if you are already in nyc the landlord has given her the keys to show people the unit so I can connect you with her.

If interested, please message me a brief description of who you are and what you do!

text:
IF YOU ARE a CLASSICAL PIANIST or a MUSICIAN, it's dream place for you! You can practice ANY time of the day/night 24/7 on gorgeous completely rebuilt Steinway O by The Klavierhaus, hold concerts-solo or chamber music, rehearsals, teach, or hold master classes right in your own room. Now, available from March 1 2021

---Hi, Manhattan UWS near Columbia University, beautiful safe neighborhood, secure 24/7 doorman Pre-War elevator building, OWN private bedroom, with PRIVATE SEPARATE ENTRANCE from me, both to the apartment itself, and to the room, and it would be like having 2/3 the apartment to yourself, very much like having your own private studio apartment, except for sharing full kitchen, dining, and bathrooms, and, IF YOU ARE a CLASSICAL PIANIST or a MUSICIAN, it's dream place for you! You can practice ANY time of the day/night 24/7 on gorgeous completely rebuilt Steinway O by The Klavierhaus, hold concerts, rehearsals, teach, or hold master classes right in your own room. High floor 15th, beautiful view of Empire State building, some view of Hudson river and the East side, quiet, high enough away from the street noise, and very sound proof enough that we won't hear each other even with doors open, me, classical professional violinist, unless we purposely go to the other side of the apartment. Yes, that far away, that private, and that sound proof. It will even be hard to know whether each other is even in.

Long term sublet. MINIMUM 3 MONTHS to hopefully YEARS, longer the better, flexible dates, no fee

Interns, students (including INTERNATIONAL), musicians, dream for pianists, all welcome (I am internationally recognized classical concert violinist and professor, but you wonâ€™t hear me, if you close your door). Interns, students (including international), musicians, dream for pianists, all welcome (I am internationally recognized classical concert violinist and professor, but you wonâ€™t hear me, if you close your door).

I'm looking to sublet the bigger of the 2 private rooms (the room in the first picture with piano. Now, the full size bed is hidden behind a room divider) which used to double as my guest room, the concert hall, and as my music studio, for LONG term with flexible dates, for male/female (it wouldn't matter because I am on one end of the apartment, and the sublessee would be on the opposite end, completely separated by the kitchen and a hallway to the bathroom, with separate entrance) non-smoker. The only pic that is not here is my own room which is at the opposite end of the apartment from the room here shown with the piano-the room which I am subletting. There are some additional chairs along the wall (used to be my music, concert room) not shown in the picture, because they are on the sides of the wall behind the door.

The occupancy is for SINGLE OCCUPANCY only (periodic visitors including overnights are of course fine but no residencies). No illegal drugs or smoking of any kind, and MUST TAKE SHOES OFF upon entering the apartment.

It is a huge, fully-furnished own private lockable room with gorgeous view of Broadway (beautiful view of the Empire State building) and the Hudson River. The room is bright and sunny and simply HUMONGOUS: 12'9" x 24'5"!

The apartment is located on the 15th floor of a 24-hr doorman elevator building, steps away from Columbia University. This is an amazing neighborhood with great supermarkets and restaurants. The 1 train and buses 7, 11, 4, 5, 60 and 104 are readily accessible. And if you're a runner or a park lover, you will especially enjoy the apartment's proximity to Central Park and Riverside Park. If you are a pianist or musician, it is dream come true with the optional unlimited use of the newly rebuilt Steinway O Grand Piano for extra $25 per month (can practice at any time of the day, very soundproof)

Must supply me web-links (i.e. LinkedIn, Facebook etc.) which will tell me as much about yourself as is possible and/or references.

The rent is all inclusive at $1760 except for the use of the Steinway Grand Piano (available for extra fee as above)

- Fully-furnished own room 12'9" x 24'5"!, with a full size bed
- Wireless and Ethernet Internet
- basic antennae TV
- Air Conditioner
- Washer and Dryer in the APARTMENT (as long as it lasts)
-- Private SEPARATE Entrance with much privacy. You will be on one side of the apartment, and I on the other side, completely separated by the kitchen and a hallway to the bathroom, it will be like you have 2/3 of the whole apartment to yourself
- IJoy massage chair (as long as it lasts)
- FULL use of the kitchen and utensils, share bathroom
- ALL utilities included

The room will be available for long term rental. A deposit of one monthâ€™s rent and the first full month's rent, in addition to any partial month rent, if entered mid-month, is required in cash to move in. Subsequent payments can be personal check or cash. If interested, please email me and arrange for a viewing. Only serious inquiries please. Thank you and good luck!

Spacious two bedroom in the Upper West Side !
- High ceilings and hardwood floors
- spacious living area
- open kitchen layout with plenty of counter space
- spacious bedrooms
- marble tiled bathrooms
- doorman
- elevator

The Upper West Side is full of beautifully maintained brownstones, safe & quiet tree lined streets and impeccably maintained parks and public space! Sandwiched between Columbia University and Lincoln Center, everything you could want for is available at your fingertips. From music venues, rooftop bars, top notch restaurant, there are quiet coffee shops and hidden secrets around every corner. Blessed with two subway lines and several express stops, commuting is a breeze. One thing not to forget is that the UWS is lined with Riverside Park to the West and Central Park to the east. Own a pet or just enjoy the green space? This is the neighborhood for you! Look no further, you've found your new neighborhood!

Looking to sublet my room starting as soon as possible and ending on 06/30/2021. Rent is $1,300 and includes all utilities except internet. Internet on its own is $16.67 each month. The apartment has 3 bedrooms, a large kitchen, and an even larger living room. The bedroom has it's own A/C unit and radiator for heat with a thermostat in the room to adjust the temperature. The room is large enough to fit a Queen sized by and a corner desk with plenty of empty space to avoid feeling claustrophobic. There's also a ton of closet space that easily fits an overcoat, 5 suits, plenty of button-up shirts and pants, 3 vests, and an extra jacket along with shelf space.

The apartment is located on the main street in Roosevelt Island. You can quickly access both Queens and Manhattan by using the F train that's about a 5 minute walk away from the apartment. Manhattan can also be accessed by the tram that's about a 10 minute walk away from the apartment.

The security deposit would be $1,400. The total rent and utilities are split with 2 other male roommates in their mid 20s who work as consultants.

This apartment features
-Exposed brick wall
-Fireplace
-Loft storage
-Walking distance to Riverside park
-Lots of natural light

The Upper West Side is full of beautifully maintained brownstones, safe & quiet tree lined streets and impeccably maintained parks and public space! Sandwiched between Columbia University and Lincoln Center, everything you could want for is available at your fingertips. From music venues, rooftop bars, top notch restaurant, there are quiet coffee shops and hidden secrets around every corner. Blessed with two subway lines and several express stops, commuting is a breeze. One thing not to forget is that the UWS is lined with Riverside Park to the West and Central Park to the east. Own a pet or just enjoy the green space? This is the neighborhood for you! Look no further, you've found your new neighborhood!

text:
NO FEE: 3.5 Bedroom 2 Bathroom Floor-Through Apartment for Rent in Cobble Hill Brooklyn Townhouse!

Need more space in an incredible neighborhood? Step into this massive, bright 3.5 bed 2 bath dream! This apartment is nothing short of stunning, from the decorative molding in the living room, to the wide plank floors and exposed brick in the master bedroom. The kitchen is as modern as anyone would hope, featuring a stainless steel appliances, including dishwasher. Not only are all 3 bedrooms quite large, but each is complete with storage for all of your belongings. Each bathroom features subway tile, modern sinks, and bathtubs. The eat-in kitchen leads into the large living room with an extra smaller room off the side- perfect for an office, guest room or playroom. This is a truly stunning space in the heart of Cobble Hill- it's not to be missed!

There is laundry in the building that is just for this apartment and one other unit as well.

Hello!

I am looking for a roommate (or two) to find a place in Manhattan in mid-august or September 1. I am looking for a 12mo lease and looking for places mostly uptown. I have a position at a private school located in Westchester, but I'll be doing WFH for the indefinite future.

A short bit about me: LGBTQ cis male, recent Bowdoin College graduate, moved to the city for a sublease at the beginning of the summer, but I am now aiming for a year-long lease. I am an athlete with NYAC, so I am looking for other people who enjoy going out and being active. I love cooking, but I also love finding new places. Not huge into going out, but I can appreciate a small bar crawl.

Feel free to message me and we can go from there!

text:
Hi everyone, one of my current roommates is moving out on October 31st so my roommates and I are looking for someone to fill his spot!
About the apartment:
Rent/ Security: $990 (utilities not included)
Huge apartment located in Williamsburg only steps from Domino Park. The apartment is a 5 bedroom 1 bath and only 8-10 min walk to the JMZ and L trains. Many bars, restaurants, etc. There is full laundry access in the building and we have a dishwasher as well. We also have the sweetest little cat named Fallow and would prefer someone with no animals. There is additionally full rooftop access with amazing views of the east river!
About the roommates:
You'll be living with 4 other roommates (all guys) who work full time. We are a fun group who enjoys hanging out but are respectful of each others personal time/space and like to keep the place clean. Our ages range from 23-25. We are doing as much as possible during COVID to stay safe so we are expecting the same from you. Must be LGBTQ+ friendly!
If interested please feel free to reach out!!

Best location, best roof!
This beautiful and bright two-bedroom apartment is in the heart of downtown Manhattan! Have easy access to Times Square, Chinatown, Little Italy, Flatiron, Union Square, and much much more.
The best about this home is its killer roof access which you can't get in any hotels or NYC apartments. Plus its fully furnished functional spaces gives you everything you need- from a full kitchen access and cozy dining area, to comfy beds and sofa bed.
You'll also be in an elevator + laundry building for your convenience. Great accommodation and appliances including WiFi, air conditioning, refrigerator, washer, dryer, microwave, dishwasher, coffee maker, cooking basics, and more for $3100/month. Normally this apartment goes for $3500 for long term stay with no furnishings and broker fee.
It will be available starting January 10 to July 2021. Sublet criteria is flexible and preferably stay would be for the entire time.
Don't hesitate to send me a private message for more info and if interested! Thank you!

Good evening to all !

I want to donate my property worth 4,674,800 euros to any person of good faith, honesty and need. In short, my name is Enet Patricia, of French origin and I suffer from a serious illness that condemns me to death. It is a neck cancer and I have an amount of 4,674,800 euros that I would like to donate to an honest and trustworthy person to use at the end. from a Belgian, Italian, Swiss import company ... and I lost my husband a few years ago, six years that touched me a lot and I couldn't remarry until today, I had no children. I would like to donate this amount before my death, so that my days can be taken into account for the absence of this disease that I did not have. remedy
I ask all those interested to contact E-Mail: enetpatricia2@gmail.com

text:
Hi! We are leaving our beautiful 2-bedrooms / 1 bathroom apartment and are looking for someone to take over our lease for the 6 months remaining, with possibility to renew it (the landlord will propose a lease renewal end of May)

We love this place. The layout is extremely convenient, the apartment is easy to furnish. The open kitchen is fully equipped with stainless steel appliances (new fridge), ample storage, and counter space. Bedrooms can accommodate full-sized beds and extra furnishing and get great natural sunlight (2 windows in each room).
This is a perfect apartment for roomates and even better for a couple: we're using the second bedroom as a walk-in closet.

The apartment is located in Bushwick (Evergreen Ave & Willoughby Ave), M train at Central Ave (4 min walk) and M, J, Z trains at Myrtle-Broadway (8 min walk). 15 min walking distance from Morgan Ave and Jefferson St. Lots of options for supermarkets, grocery stores, cool bars and restaurants,laundries etc.

Price is $2,000/month (excluding utilities).

Please DM me for any additional information.

Im moving across the country and have a large bedroom available in a $ bed 1.5 bathroom apartment, located in Bed Stuy/ Crown Heights for $845, +$50 utilities, and $10 WiFi a month. An $845 refundable deposit will be required as well as first months rent for move in. This would be a room of your own!

There are three other roommates in this 4 bed, 1.5 bath unit. The lease ends in June 2021 with the option to extend or renew.

About the room:
- The bedroom is 10ft x 12ft
- We can put the AC back into the window if preferred
- Central Heating and A/C as well as an A/C in the bedroom
- In walking distance from the C (Rockaway) and the J (Chauncey St station) also the L (Bushwick Av-Aberdeen St)
- Not wheelchair accessible
- On the second floor of the building. The first floor and basement are occupied by other tenants; we have an entrance way that splits to three door entrances.
-Very spacious apartment with tons or natural light and a skylight
-Backyard

Reach out for a video tour and meet the other roommates!

Guarantors accepted! LGBTQ and BIPOC Friendly!
